text.tspan: "Files" don't have names. The descriptions are stored as "path" properties
on the "contains" relationships between "Spots". (Spot is used rather than
Directory because a Spot can have both content as well as containing other
Spots simultaneously.) Ideally, all coherent paths should resolve to a given resource.
an IPFS CID of the contents. When a new File
is added at a particular Point, a "replaces"

tspan.tspan: relationship is created to the previous embodiment

text.tspan: of that Noopoint. The current version is the one
that has not been replaced by any other Files.
In the graph, a particular concept is represented by a "Noopoint".
The Noosphere is the space of all possible concepts, so a point in
that space is a particular thing. (The book "Shoggoths in Bloom"
by E. Bear in this example.)
The "replaces" relationships have a UUID for the changeset that
introduced the new File as well as a timestamp for when the

tspan.tspan: changes were added. Finding the state of the system at a given
moment involves examining the replaces relationships and finding

text.tspan: versions of Files that existed at that point in time.
